This paper deals with the neural coding of spatiotemporal spike patterns, which is a topic closely related to computational neuroscience and neural networks. The use of spike-timing-dependent plasticity (STDP) and coincidence detection also suggests a focus on neural network models. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Other likely sub-categories include cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), as these sub-categories also cover topics related to neural networks and computational neuroscience.
